text:
East Broadway, west from and including Rutgers Street.
September 24, 1927.

P. L. Sperr.

Rutgers Street, east side, south from East Broadway. The 6-story corner building is No. 7 Rutgers Street and 163 East Broadway.

June 6, 1930.

P. L. Sperr.

(1)
6-10 Rutgers Street, at, adjoining, and south of the S.W. corner of East Broadway. The two buildings, Nos. 8-10 will be renovated. On the extreme left appears a portion of St. Teresa's R.C. Church, located at the N.W. corner of Henry Street.
April 20, 1931.

P. L. Sperr.

(2)
The same, at a later date.
March 19, 1934.

P. L. Sperr.
